In [[physics]], the '''Einstein&ndash;Hopf drag''' (named after [[Albert Einstein]] and [[Ludwig Hopf]]) is a velocity-dependent [[drag (physics)|drag]] [[force]] upon charged particles that are being bathed in thermal radiation.<ref>{{cite book|title=Gravitation and Cosmology: From the Hubble Radius to the Planck Scale|author=Jean-Pierre Vigier and Richard L. Amoroso|pages=119|year=2002|publisher=Springer|isbn=1-4020-0885-6}}</ref>

