:{{note label|Hestercombe|D|D}}Size smaller than can be shown with one decimal place. Actual size: 0.08 ha.<ref name="data"/>
:{{note label|Severn Estuary|E|E}}The Severn Estuary SSSI overlaps with the following SSSIs:<ref name="data"/>
::*Avon: [[Spring Cove Cliffs]], [[Middle Hope]], [[Portishead Pier to Black Nore SSSI|Portishead Pier to Black Nore]] and [[Aust Cliff]].
::*Gloucestershire: [[Purton Passage]]
::*South Glamorgan: [[Penarth Coast]]
:{{note label|Severn Estuary date|F|F}}Incorporates two former SSSIs: Severn Estuary (notified 1976) and part of Brean Down and Uphill Cliff (notified 1952). It was unified as Severn Estuary in 1989.<ref name="data"/>
:{{note label|Wookey Station|G|G}}Size smaller than can be shown with one decimal place. Actual size: 0.04 ha. (0.1 ac.).<ref name="data"/>
:{{note label|Long Dole|H|H}}The Long Dole Wood and Meadows site extends into [[Bath and North East Somerset]] and so can be found on the list of [[List of Sites of Special Scientific Interest in Avon|SSSIs in Avon]].<ref name="data"/>

