{{Infobox Lunar mare
|name        = Palus Putredinus
|image       = [[Image:Palus-putredinis-clem1.jpg|300px|Palus Putredinus]]
|caption     = [[Clementine (spacecraft)|Clementine]] image
|coordinates = {{coord|26.5|N|0.4|E|globe:moon_type:landmark|display=inline,title}}
|diameter    = 161 km
|eponym      = Marsh of Decay
}}

'''Palus Putredinus''' ([[Latin]] for "Marsh of Decay") is an area of the [[Moon|lunar]] surface that stretches from the crater [[Archimedes (crater)|Archimedes]] southeast toward the rugged [[Montes Apenninus]] range located on the southeastern edge of [[Mare Imbrium]]. This region is a nearly level, [[lava]]-flooded plain bounded by the crater [[Autolycus (crater)|Autolycus]] to the north and the foothills of the [[Montes Archimedes]] to the west. The selenographic [[coordinate]]s are 26.5° N, 0.4° E, and it lies within a diameter of 161&nbsp;km.

In the southern part of this area is a [[rille]] system designated Rimae Archimedes. To the south is a prominent linear rille named Rima Bradley, and to the east is the Rima Hadley, which served as the landing site for [[Apollo 15]], and the Rimae Fresnel. Just to the northwest of the Palus Putredinus midpoint is the nearly submerged crater [[Spurr (crater)|Spurr]]. [[Luna 2]] crashed in this area.

